\begin_layout Standard
The regional unit of Attica covers an area of 3,808.1 km²,
 with Athens as its capital.
 Between 2001 and 2025,
 Attica experienced a loss of 22 kha (220 km²) of tree cover attributable to wildfires,
 along with an additional 3.3 kha (33 km²) lost due to other disturbance factors.
 The most severe year within this period was 2021,
 during which fires accounted for 8.5 kha (85 km²) of tree cover loss,
 representing 99% of the total loss recorded that year,
 according to the global forest watch 
