 the findings of the study identified new threshold values for wildfire occurrence in the region of Attica,
 as follows:
 temperature ≥ 73.7 °F,
 humidity ≤ 49.3%,
 0% precipitation,
 wind gust speed ≥ 10.01 mph,
 wind speed ≥ 16.1 mph,
 wind direction in the sectors SW,
 N,
 NE,
 and NW,
 ignition time from 12:31 on wards,
 and hazardous months corresponding to June,
 July,
 and August*.
\end_layout

