The regional unit of Crete covers an area of 8.450 km²,
 with Herakleio as its capital.
 Between 2001 to 2025 Crete experienced a loss of 1.3 kha (13 km²) of tree cover attributable to wildfires,
 along with an additional 3.2 kha (33 km²) lost due to other disturbance factors.
 The most severe year within this period was 2008 during which fires accounted for 210 ha (2.1 km²) of tree cover loss,
